===Team base camps===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup base camps}}

Base camps were used by the 48 squads to stay and train at before and during the World Cup tournament.<ref name="Team Base camps">{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/base-camps-potential-locations |title=FIFA shares potential World Cup 26 Team Base Camp locations|access-date=June 12, 2024 |website=fifa.com |date=June 12, 2024|archive-date=June 12, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240612215436/https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/base-camps-potential-locations|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://inside.fifa.com/about-fifa/organisation/news/fifa-world-cup-26-tm-expands-team-base-camp-brochure-26-new-options-added |title=FIFA World Cup 26 expands Team Base Camp brochure: 26 new options added |publisher=FIFA |date=November 21, 2024 |access-date=January 15, 2025 |archive-date=November 21, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241121220113/https://inside.fifa.com/about-fifa/organisation/news/fifa-world-cup-26-tm-expands-team-base-camp-brochure-26-new-options-added |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://inside.fifa.com/organisation/news/14-new-team-base-camp-options-world-cup-2026 |title=14 new Team Base Camp options added as road to 2026 continues |date=April 17, 2025 |website=inside.fifa.com|archive-date=April 17, 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250417180742/https://inside.fifa.com/organisation/news/14-new-team-base-camp-options-world-cup-2026|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Schirgi |first=Heimo |title=Team Base Camp brochure |url=https://fwc26teambasecamps.fifa.com |access-date=October 23, 2025 |website=FIFA}}</ref>

===Squads===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup squads}}

Before submitting their final squad for the tournament, teams named a provisional squad of between 35 and 55 players one month prior to the tournament. Teams were required to name their final squads by June 2. If a player becomes too injured or ill to prevent his participation in the tournament, he can be replaced by another player from the provisional squad until 24 hours before the team's first match. However, an injured or ill goalkeeper may be replaced by another goalkeeper from the provisional squad at any time during the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/squad-lists-number-date |title=When are World Cup squads named, and how many players will feature? |publisher=[[FIFA]] |date=May 6, 2026 |access-date=May 7, 2026}}</ref>

==Officiating==
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup officials}}

On April 9, 2026, [[FIFA]] announced the list of 52 referees, 88 assistant referees, and 30 [[video assistant referee]]s for the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |date=April 9, 2026 |title=Match officials appointed for World Cup 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/match-officials-appointed-referees |access-date=April 9, 2026 |website=FIFA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=April 9, 2026 |title=List of appointed FIFA Match Officials |url=https://digitalhub.fifa.com/asset/7879a8c6-c228-4848-a8de-7dc69b37b594/Final-List-of-Match-Officials-FWC-2026.pdf |access-date=April 9, 2026 |website=FIFA}}</ref>

==Ceremonies==
===Opening ceremonies===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup opening ceremonies}}

The tournament featured three opening ceremonies, one for each of the hosts.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2026 World Cup Opening Ceremonies: How to Watch, Who is Performing, Start Times |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/2026-world-cup-opening-ceremonies-how-watch-who-performing-start-times |access-date=June 11, 2026 |website=www.foxsports.com |language=en-US}}</ref> The opening ceremony in Mexico took place on June 11, 2026, at Estadio Banorte.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c2ly928xz8go|title= World Cup kicks off in Mexico with Shakira, dancing, and protests|date=June 12, 2026|work=BBC News|accessdate=June 13, 2026}}</ref> Mexican singer [[Alejandro Fernández]] performed "[[Himno Nacional Mexicano]]" and South African singer [[Tyla]] performed the "[[National anthem of South Africa]]"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inside.fifa.com/organisation/media-releases/origin1904-p.cxm.fifa.com/more-special-guests-revealed-world-cup-2026-ceremonies-mexico-city|title=More special guests revealed for FIFA World Cup 2026™ ceremonies in Mexico City|website=inside.fifa.com}}</ref> The next day, on June 12, 2026, the opening ceremony in Canada took place at BMO Field in Toronto. Canadian-American musician [[Alanis Morissette]] performed "[[O Canada]]" while Serbian-Canadian violinist Aleksandar Gajić performed "[[National anthem of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Državna himna Bosne i Hercegovine]]".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inside.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/media-releases/origin1904-p.cxm.fifa.com/expanded-lineup-revealed-world-cup-2026-tm-ceremonies-canada|title=Expanded lineup revealed for FIFA World Cup 2026™ ceremonies in Canada|website=inside.fifa.com}}</ref> On the same day, the opening ceremony for the United States took place at SoFi Stadium in Los Angeles. American country duo [[Dan + Shay]] performed "[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]" while Paraguayan soul duo Purahei Soul performed "[[Paraguayan National Anthem|Himno Nacional Paraguayo]]".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inside.fifa.com/organisation/media-releases/origin1904-p.cxm.fifa.com/additional-talent-unveiled-world-cup-2026-ceremonies-los-angeles|title=Additional talent unveiled for FIFA World Cup 2026™ ceremonies in Los Angeles|website=inside.fifa.com}}</ref>

===Independence Day ceremonies===
In addition, two special ceremonies will take place on July 4, 2026, to honor the [[United States Semiquincentennial]] at [[Lincoln Financial Field]] in Philadelphia and [[NRG Stadium]] in Houston.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7262593/2026/05/08/fifa-opening-ceremonies-perry-buble-america-250/|title=FIFA to hold three World Cup opening ceremonies and two marking America 250, artists revealed|first=Adam|last=Crafton|work=The New York Times |date=May 8, 2026|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>

==Group stage==
[[File:2026 world cup.svg|thumb|Result of countries participating in the 2026 FIFA World Cup{{Legend|#ff0000|Round of 32}}{{Legend|#A00000|Group stage}}]]
The [[round-robin tournament|round-robin]] group stage is being played in twelve groups (A to L) of four teams from June 11 to 27.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Scores & Fixtures |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/scores-fixtures |access-date=December 10, 2025 |website=FIFA}}</ref> Teams are awarded three points for a win, one for a draw, and none for a loss. Following the conclusion of group play, the top two teams of each group, along with the [[#Ranking of third-placed teams|eight best third-placed teams]], will advance to the [[#Knockout stage|knockout stage]].

