===Group A===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group A}}

In the opening match of the tournament, co-host [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] faced [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa]]. [[Julián Quiñones]] opened the scoring for Mexico within ten minutes, and [[Raúl Jiménez]] scored Mexico's second goal to achieve a 2–0 victory. Three direct red cards (the most in a World Cup opening match) were given during the game, one each to [[Sphephelo Sithole]] and [[Themba Zwane]] of South Africa, and one to Mexico's [[César Montes]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Raghuraman |first=Anantaajith |date=June 12, 2026 |title=Breaking down the dirtiest World Cup opening game we've ever seen – or was it? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7352942/2026/06/11/world-cup-mexico-south-africa-red-cards/ |access-date=June 12, 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> On the same day, [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] defeated [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/jun/12/south-korea-czechia-world-cup-2026-group-a-match-report|title=South Korea get off to winning start after rallying from goal down to beat Czechia|date=June 12, 2026|work=Guardian|accessdate=June 14, 2026}}</ref>

Facing South Africa, the Czech Republic took the lead early on thanks to [[Michal Sadílek]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gamble |first=Andrew |date=June 18, 2026 |title=Furious World Cup viewers slam official's decision and cry 'the game is gone' |url=https://www.themirror.com/sport/soccer/czechia-south-africa-world-cup-1894607 |access-date=June 18, 2026 |website=The Mirror US |language=en}}</ref> [[Teboho Mokoena (soccer, born 1997)|Teboho Mokoena]] converted a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]] to equalize the score and produce a draw.<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Cardenas |first1=Felipe |last2=Ballús |first2=Pol |date=June 18, 2026 |title=South Africa holds Czech Republic – was it the worst game of the World Cup? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7365808/2026/06/18/czech-republic-south-africa-world-cup-2026-score-results-takeaways/ |access-date=June 18, 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Mexico defeated South Korea and became the first team to qualify for the knockout stage.<ref>{{Cite news |last=T |last2=h |last3=e |last4=A |last5=s |last6=s |last7=o |last8=c |last9=i |date=June 19, 2026 |title=Mexico becomes first country to reach knockout stage of World Cup |url=https://www.npr.org/2026/06/19/g-s1-129056/mexico-becomes-first-country-to-reach-knockout-stage-of-world-cup |access-date=June 19, 2026 |work=NPR |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Arnold |first=Jon |title=Mexico's Luis Romo scores World Cup goal on shocking goalkeeper blunder |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/worldcup/2026/06/18/luis-romo-goal-mexico-on-south-korea-goalkeeper/90518412007/ |access-date=June 19, 2026 |website=USA TODAY |language=en-US}}</ref>{{2026 FIFA World Cup group tables|Group A|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}

