===Group B===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group B}}

In Group B, co-host [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] opened its World Cup campaign against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. [[Jovo Lukić]] of Bosnia scored during the first half, while [[Cyle Larin]] of Canada scored during the second half. The draw gave Canada its first-ever World Cup point.<ref name=":8">{{Cite web |last=Horswill |first=Chloe |date=June 12, 2026 |title=Canada 1-1 Bosnia-Herzegovina Stats: Super-Sub Larin Secures Late Point for Co-Hosts |url=https://theanalyst.com/articles/canada-vs-bosnia-herzegovina-stats-world-cup-2026 |access-date=June 12, 2026 |website=Opta Analyst |language=en}}</ref> [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] opened its campaign against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] with a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] by [[Breel Embolo]] despite offside claims.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |title=Qatar's miracle late goal delivers draw vs. Switzerland |url=https://fieldlevelmedia.com/news/qatars-miracle-late-goal-delivers-draw-vs-switzerland/ |access-date=June 14, 2026 |website=Field Level Media - Professional sports content solutions {{!}} FLM |language=en-US}}</ref> However, Switzerland conceded a late equalizing goal after [[Miro Muheim]] accidentally deflected the ball into the Swiss net, giving Qatar its first-ever World Cup point.<ref name=":4" />

Switzerland played Bosnia and Herzegovina to a scoreless first half in their match. In the 74th minute, [[Johan Manzambi]] broke the deadlock. [[Rubén Vargas]] followed up shortly after [[Tarik Muharemović]] was sent off. Manzambi scored a brace in the 90th minute, and [[Ermin Mahmić]] scored Bosnia's lone goal before conceding a penalty converted by [[Granit Xhaka]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Switzerland beat Bosnia 4-1 in Group B match |url=http://breakingthenews.net/Article/Switzerland-beat-Bosnia-4-1-in-Group-B-match/66536466 |access-date=June 18, 2026 |website=breakingthenews.net |language=en}}</ref> Canada won its first-ever World Cup match against Qatar, with a final score of 6–0 thanks to a hat trick from [[Jonathan David]], goals from Cyle Larin and [[Nathan Saliba]], and an own goal by [[Mohamed Manai]]. Qatari players [[Homam Ahmed]] and [[Assim Madibo]] both received red cards, the latter for a late challenge from behind on [[Ismaël Koné]], which fractured both the [[fibula]] and [[tibia]] of the Canadian's left leg.<ref>{{Cite news |first=John |last=Vennavally-Rao |title=Medical experts provide opinion on how long it will take for Canada’s Koné to recover |publisher=[[CTV News]] |date=June 19, 2026 |url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/health/article/canadas-kone-has-long-road-ahead-after-world-cup-injury-doctors-say/ |access-date=June 20, 2026}}</ref>

