===Group C===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group C}}

[[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] took the lead over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] early in the first half with a goal from [[Ismael Saibari]]; Brazil responded quickly with a goal from [[Vinícius Júnior]] 11 minutes later. The second half produced no further goals and the two ultimately earned a point apiece.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Brazil struggle with World Cup 'nerves' in Morocco draw |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/49054529/brazil-vs-morocco-2026-world-cup-vinicius-junior |access-date=June 14, 2026 |website=www.espn.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=AFP |title=Vinicius drags low-key Brazil level against dominant Morocco at World Cup |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/6/14/vinicius-drags-brazil-level-against-dominant-morocco-at-world-cup |access-date=June 14, 2026 |website=Al Jazeera |language=en}}</ref> Meanwhile, [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] bested [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] to top the group after the first matchday, with [[John McGinn]]'s first half goal proving enough to record Scotland's first World Cup match victory since [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Canavan |first1=Amy |title=Haiti 0–1 Scotland: Match Report |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c4gy7dxk0xwt |access-date=June 14, 2026 |work=BBC Sport Scotland |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=June 13, 2026 |location=Gillette Stadium (Boston Stadium)}}</ref>

An early goal 71 seconds into the match from [[Ismael Saibari]] gave Morocco the lead over Scotland. Despite efforts from Scotland to equalize, Morocco dominated the game.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tạp chí Bóng Đá, Báo Bóng Đá, kết quả, lịch thi đấu, video bàn thắng, nhận định, tỷ lệ - Bongdaplus.vn |url=https://bongdaplus.vn/ |access-date=June 20, 2026 |website=bongdaplus.vn |language=vi}}</ref> Haiti started its match against Brazil with resilient, high-tempo play, but three goals conceded in the first half to [[Vinícius Júnior]] and [[Matheus Cunha]] sealed the Haitians' departure from the World Cup, being the first team to be eliminated.<ref>{{Cite web |title=World Cup: Haiti become first team eliminated as Brazil win 3-0 |url=https://www.chinadailyhk.com/hk/article/635252#World-Cup%3A-Haiti-become-first-team-eliminated-as-Brazil-win-3-0--2026-06-20 |access-date=June 20, 2026 |website=chinadailyhk |language=en}}</ref>

