===Group D===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group D}}

In Group D, co-host [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] faced [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] in its opening match. In the first ten minutes, the United States scored off a deflection from Paraguay's [[Damián Bobadilla]]. [[Folarin Balogun]] debuted with two goals in the first half, scoring the United States' first World Cup [[Brace (association football)|brace]] since [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]. In the second half, [[Maurício (footballer, born 2001)|Maurício]] reduced the deficit for Paraguay, but the United States' [[Giovanni Reyna]] scored a stoppage-time [[Curl (association football)|curled shot]] to finish proceedings. The co-host scored more goals in this match (four) than it did during the entire [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] (three).<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sullivan |first=Becky |date=June 12, 2026 |title=The U.S. dazzles in its World Cup opener, dominating Paraguay 4-1 |url=https://www.npr.org/2026/06/12/nx-s1-5850736/2026-world-cup-usmnt-paraguay |access-date=June 13, 2026 |work=NPR |language=en}}</ref> [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] won its opener against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] 2–0. Although Turkey had possession of the ball for the majority of the game, Australia's [[Nestory Irankunda]] scored in the first half, and [[Connor Metcalfe]] added another goal in the second.<ref>{{Cite news |date=June 14, 2026 |title=Socceroos ecstasy as wondergoals deliver 2-0 World Cup victory over Türkiye |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2026-06-14/world-cup-live-updates-australia-vs-turkiye-socceroos/106796000 |access-date=June 14, 2026 |work=ABC News |language=en-AU}}</ref>

Despite the absence of [[Christian Pulisic]], the United States defeated Australia 2–0, clinching a spot in the knockout stage. Australia once again allowed the opposition to dominate possession; however, the tactic backfired as an early [[Cameron Burgess]] own goal and an [[Alex Freeman]] header saw the United States earn consecutive World Cup victories for the first time since [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=June 19, 2026 |title=Pulisic sits, but U.S. finds a way vs. Australia to reach World Cup KO rounds |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/49119070/christian-pulisic-sits-us-finds-way-vs-australia-reach-world-cup-knockout-rounds |access-date=June 19, 2026 |work=ESPN |language=en-US}}</ref> Turkey was eliminated after a 1–0 loss to
Paraguay. Just 64 seconds into the match, [[Matías Galarza (Paraguayan footballer)|Matías Galarza]] scored from a long-range shot outside of the box, becoming the quickest goal scored at the 2026 World Cup to that point. Despite a halftime red card to [[Miguel Almirón]] for covering his mouth during a confrontation with [[Mert Müldür]], Turkey failed to score, leading to its elimination.<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 20, 2026 |title=World Cup 2026: Turkey crash out after 1-0 defeat to ten-man Paraguay |url=https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20260620-turkey-crash-out-after-1-0-defeat-to-ten-man-paraguay |access-date=June 20, 2026 |website=France 24 |language=en}}</ref>

