===Group E===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group E}}

[[Germany national football team|Germany]] began its campaign against debutant [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]]. [[Felix Nmecha]] scored for the Germans within the first six minutes, but the Curaçaoans scored an equalizer thanks to [[Livano Comenencia]], seeing Curaçao's first ever World Cup goal, in its first ever World Cup game. Later goals by [[Nico Schlotterbeck]], [[Jamal Musiala]], [[Nathaniel Brown (footballer)|Nathaniel Brown]], and [[Deniz Undav]], along with [[Kai Havertz|Kai Havertz's]] brace, sealed a 7–1 victory for the Germans.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ames |first=Nick |date=June 14, 2026 |title=Curaçao enjoy their moment but Havertz and ruthless Germany show no mercy |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/jun/14/germany-curacao-world-cup-match-report |access-date=June 15, 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[Amad Diallo]] scored a late winner for [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]], securing a 1–0 victory over [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] as the latter failed to capitalize on its chances.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ames |first=Nick |date=June 14, 2026 |title=Ivory Coast 1-0 Ecuador: Amad scores late winner as Ecuador rue misses - as it happened |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/49064087/ivory-coast-ecuador-live-world-cup-2026-latest-updates-commentary-score-result |access-date=June 15, 2026 |work=ESPN |language=en-US }}</ref>

Germany secured a spot in the knockout stage for the first time since [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]] after beating Ivory Coast 2–1. The first half saw a goal from [[Franck Kessié]] after the Germans saw 2 goals disallowed from foul calls. In the second half, [[Julian Nagelsmann|Nagelsmann]] made a triple substitution, which turned the tide for the game. [[Deniz Undav]] scored the equaliser from a cross from [[Nadiem Amiri]], and scored a late winner to send the Germans into the knockouts.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Athletic |first=The |date=June 20, 2026 |title=Deniz Undav double sees Germany beat Ivory Coast at the death in 2026 World Cup thriller: Live updates and reaction |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/germany-vs-ivory-coast-live-updates-world-cup-2026-score-result/ARDIuH2TBoAU/ |access-date=June 21, 2026 |website=The Athletic |language=en-US}}</ref> Ecuador was held to a 0–0 draw against Curaçao. Despite having 15 shots on target, Ecuador failed to find the back of the net due to Curaçao's disciplined defense and [[Eloy Room]]'s heroics, earning him a 10 match rating on [[Sofascore]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sofascore |title=Ecuador vs Curaçao live score, H2H and lineups {{!}} Sofascore |url=https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/curacao-ecuador/hVbsCqx |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20260616011934/https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/curacao-ecuador/hVbsCqx |archive-date=June 16, 2026 |access-date=June 21, 2026 |website=www.sofascore.com |language=en}}</ref>{{2026 FIFA World Cup group tables|Group E|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}

