===Group G===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group G}}

[[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] started off against [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]], conceding in the 19th minute by [[Emam Ashour]] for his first international goal.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Rueter |first=Jeff |date=June 15, 2026 |title=Lukaku makes instant impact to force own goal and rescue draw for Belgium against Egypt |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/jun/15/belgium-egypt-world-cup-2026-group-g-match-report |access-date=June 16, 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[Romelu Lukaku]] seemingly scored an equalizer in the 66th minute after being substituted on for 23 seconds, but it was ruled an own goal by [[Mohamed Hany]],<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Hughes |first1=Simon |last2=O'Keeffe |first2=Greg |last3=Carey |first3=Mark |date=June 15, 2026 |title=Lukaku's impact keeps Egypt waiting for World Cup win but do Belgium's old guard still cut it? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7359748/2026/06/15/belgium-egypt-highlights-goals-lukaku/ |access-date=June 16, 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> and the two teams shared points at the end of the match. [[Iran national football team|Iran]] and [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]] traded goals throughout the match, with Iran coming from behind twice through [[Ramin Rezaeian]] and [[Mohammad Mohebi]] while [[Elijah Just]] scored a brace for the latter.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Fisher |first=Ben |date=June 16, 2026 |title=Iran twice come from behind to claim draw in World Cup opener with New Zealand |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/jun/16/iran-new-zealand-world-cup-2026-group-g-match-report |access-date=June 16, 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

Belgium and Iran both played to a goalless draw. In the 66th minute, Belgian defender [[Nathan Ngoy]] received a straight red card on the 67th minute after committing a [[DOGSO]] (denying an obvious goal-scoring opportunity) on [[Mehdi Taremi]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Vertelney |first=Seth |title=Belgium defender Nathan Ngoy gets red card after terrible error vs Iran |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/worldcup/2026/06/21/nathan-ngoy-red-card-belgium-iran-world-cup/90637191007/ |access-date=June 22, 2026 |website=USA TODAY |language=en-US}}</ref> New Zealand's [[Finn Surman]] opened the match against Egypt after 15 minutes, but second-half goals from [[Mostafa Ziko]], [[Mohamed Salah]], and [[Trézéguet (Egyptian footballer)|Trézéguet]] oversaw the team's first World Cup win since debuting back in 1934.<ref>{{Cite web |date=May 12, 2026 |title=New Zealand 1-3 Egypt: Inspired comeback seals maiden World Cup victory |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/new-zealand-1-3-egypt-inspired-comeback-seals-maiden-world-cup-victory-43042286 |access-date=June 22, 2026 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> On the other hand, the result handed New Zealand its first defeat since 1982.<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 22, 2026 |title=New Zealand Lose First World Cup Since 1982: 5 Takeaways |url=https://au.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-lists/new-zealand-lose-first-world-cup-match-since-1982-5-takeaways-97427/ |access-date=June 22, 2026 |website=Rolling Stone Australia |language=en-AU}}</ref>

