===Group I===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group I}}

[[France national football team|France]] and [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] started their match scoreless in the first half amid wasted chances from both sides, along with [[Ismaïla Sarr]] missing an open chance from six yards out by hitting the ball over the bar. In the second half, [[Kylian Mbappé]] broke the deadlock at the 66th minute after being denied a penalty, while [[Bradley Barcola]] scored another in the 82nd minute. [[Ibrahim Mbaye]] scored for Senegal in stoppage time, but Mbappé scored a brace immediately after.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Meade |first=Samuel |date=June 16, 2026 |title=5 talking points as Mbappe brushes off VAR drama to ignite France's World Cup |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/match-reports/france-senegal-world-cup-highlights-37305975 |access-date=June 16, 2026 |website=Daily Mirror |language=en}}</ref> [[Norway national football team|Norway]] faced [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]], which was playing in the World Cup for the first time since 1986. [[Erling Haaland]] scored his first World Cup goal in the 29th minute, but [[Aymen Hussein]] scored an equalizer ten minutes later. Nonetheless, Haaland scored the second four minutes later; [[Leo Østigård]] and Hussein's own-goal sealed Norway's win.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rajan |first=Live ReportingAdwaidh |title=Iraq 1-4 Norway: Erling Haaland scores twice on World Cup debut |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cr5j6rn5ng2t |access-date=June 17, 2026 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

The France–Iraq game was interrupted before the start of the second half due to thunderstorms for two hours.<ref>https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20260622-world-cup-2026-france-iraq-match-suspended-as-stadium-is-evacuated-due-to-thunderstorms</ref> With wins on matchday two by France and Norway, each clinched qualification to the knockout round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/soccer/article/world-cup-2026-knockout-stage-tracker-france-argentina-and-norway-join-usa-mexico-germany-in-round-of-32-164942403.html|website=Yahoo Sports|access-date=June 22, 2026|title=World Cup 2026 knockout stage tracker: France, Argentina and Norway join USA, Mexico, Germany in Round of 32|first=Sean|last=Leahy|date=June 22, 2026}}</ref>

