===Group J===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group J}}

[[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], the defending champions from the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], faced off against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]]. [[Lionel Messi]] scored throughout the match to seal his first ever [[hat trick]] at the World Cup, also being the tournament's first. He also leveled with Germany's [[Miroslav Klose]] as the [[List of FIFA World Cup top goalscorers|joint-leading goalscorer]] in the history of the tournament with 16 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Athletic |first=The |date=June 16, 2026 |title=How sensational Lionel Messi scored his first World Cup hat-trick to lead Argentina past Algeria |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/argentina-vs-algeria-live-updates-world-cup-2026-score-result-messi/LRduTHj27ItT/ |access-date=June 17, 2026 |website=The Athletic |language=en-US}}</ref> [[Austria national football team|Austria]] and the newly debuting [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]] saw [[Romano Schmid]] score first after 20 minutes. In the second half, [[Ali Olwan]] equalized for Jordan in the 50th minute. Austria continued to struggle until an own-goal by [[Yazan Al-Arab]] and a late penalty converted by [[Marko Arnautović]] edged out Austria's victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 17, 2026 |title=Austria returns from long World Cup absence with nervy 3-1 win over debutants Jordan |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/sports/soccer/austria-returns-long-world-cup-absence-nervy-3-1-win-debutants-jordan-rcna350460 |access-date=June 17, 2026 |website=NBC News |language=en}}</ref>

