===Group K===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group K}}
The [[DR Congo national football team|Democratic Republic of the Congo]] played [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in its opener. DR Congo qualified for its first World Cup since its debut in [[1974 FIFA World Cup|1974]], when the country was known as [[Zaire]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Athletic |first=The |date=June 17, 2026 |title=DR Congo frustrate Cristiano Ronaldo's Portugal in 2026 World Cup draw: Live updates and reaction |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/portugal-vs-dr-congo-live-updates-world-cup-2026-score-result-ronaldo/eGDbBHTcwKZg/ |url-access=registration |access-date=June 18, 2026 |website=The Athletic |language=en-US}}</ref> [[João Neves]] scored for Portugal after six minutes, but near the end of the first half, [[Yoane Wissa]] scored for the DR Congo, the team's first World Cup goal. After a goalless second half, DR Congo earned its first-ever World Cup point as Portugal failed to take advantage of its chances.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ames |first=Nick |date=June 17, 2026 |title=Yoane Wissa gives DR Congo first ever World Cup point in draw with Portugal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/jun/17/portugal-dr-congo-world-cup-2026-group-k-match-report |access-date=June 18, 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] also debuted in the World Cup against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]. [[Daniel Muñoz (footballer)|Daniel Muñoz]], [[Luis Díaz (footballer, born 1997)|Luis Díaz]], and [[Jaminton Campaz]] scored for Colombia while [[Abbosbek Fayzullaev]] scored his and Uzbekistan's first World Cup goal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=authors/quinn-allen |date=June 18, 2026 |title=Colombia Beat Uzbekistan 3-1 As Luis Diaz Scores |url=https://rg.org/en-ca/news/soccer/luis-diaz-colombia-beat-uzbekistan-world-cup |access-date=June 18, 2026 |website=RG |language=en-CA}}</ref>{{2026 FIFA World Cup group tables|Group K|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}

