===Group L===
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup Group L}}[[England national football team|England]] and [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] made a fast start to the match. [[Harry Kane]] opened the scoring for England from the penalty spot, converting at the second attempt after [[Dominik Livaković]] was judged to have left his line early. The first half was played at a high tempo, with [[Martin Baturina]] and [[Petar Musa]] scoring for Croatia, while Kane added his second goal for England, leaving the teams level at 2–2 at halftime. England regained control shortly after the restart, as [[Jude Bellingham]] restored the lead two minutes into the second half before [[Marcus Rashford]] extended England's advantage.<ref>[https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/49099495/england-croatia-world-cup-2026-recap-score-harry-kane-jude-bellingham-marcus-rashford "England 4-2 Croatia: Harry Kane at the double as Three Lions start World Cup campaign with chaotic win"]. ''ESPN''. June 17, 2026. Retrieved June 17, 2026.</ref> In contrast, [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] and [[Panama national football team|Panama]] both opened the match with a goalless first half. The second half continued to see countless missed chances between the teams until [[Caleb Yirenkyi]] finally broke the deadlock in favor of Ghana five minutes into stoppage time.<ref>[https://apnews.com/article/world-cup-ghana-panama-score-a7b51c791c7568710efbbad7da8570be "Caleb Yirenki's late goal gives Ghana a 1-0 victory over Panama in the World Cup"]. ''AP News''. June 18, 2026. Retrieved June 18, 2026.</ref>{{2026 FIFA World Cup group tables|Group L|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}

