==Knockout stage==
{{Main|2026 FIFA World Cup knockout stage}}

The knockout stage will be played in a [[Single-elimination tournament|single-elimination format]], starting with the newly-introduced round of 32 on June 28 and culminating with the [[2026 FIFA World Cup final|final]] on July 19. On the day prior, a [[#Match for third place|match for third place]] will also be played. In the knockout stage, if the scores are level when normal playing time expires, 30 minutes of [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] will be played. If still tied at the end of extra time, a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] will be used to determine the winner.<ref name="regulations" />

