===FIFA fan festivals===
FIFA will stage [[FIFA Fan Festival|fan festivals]] in cities across the host nations, featuring matches on giant screens and live entertainment.<ref name="NBCNY">{{cite news |last1=Blum |first1=Ronald |title=Fan fest in Jersey City will be open for all 104 World Cup matches next year |url=https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/sports/soccer/world-cup-fan-fest-jersey-city-2026-new-york/6144761/ |access-date=March 25, 2025 |publisher=NBC New York |date=February 11, 2025|archive-date=February 12, 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250212223044/https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/sports/soccer/world-cup-fan-fest-jersey-city-2026-new-york/6144761/|url-status=live}}</ref> Among the confirmed fan fest locations are [[Liberty State Park]] in [[Jersey City, New Jersey|Jersey City]],<ref name="NBCNY" /> [[Fairmount Park]] in [[Philadelphia]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Traub |first1=Matt |title=Philadelphia to Host FIFA Fan Festival at Lemon Hill in 2026 |url=https://www.sportstravelmagazine.com/philadelphia-to-host-fifa-fan-festival-at-lemon-hill-in-2026/ |access-date=March 25, 2025 |work=SportsTravel |date=June 20, 2024 |archive-date=June 20, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620130242/https://www.sportstravelmagazine.com/philadelphia-to-host-fifa-fan-festival-at-lemon-hill-in-2026/ |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Fort York]] and [[The Bentway]] in [[Toronto]],<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.toronto.ca/news/city-of-toronto-announces-fort-york-and-the-bentway-for-its-fifa-fan-festival-location/ |title=City of Toronto announces Fort York and The Bentway for its FIFA Fan Festival location |publisher=City of Toronto |date=May 7, 2025 |access-date=May 15, 2025 |archive-date=June 1, 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250601205433/https://www.toronto.ca/news/city-of-toronto-announces-fort-york-and-the-bentway-for-its-fifa-fan-festival-location/ |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Centennial Olympic Park]] in [[Atlanta]],<ref name="fifa-atl-fan-fest-cenn">{{cite web |title=FIFA Fan Festival in Atlanta |url=https://atlantafwc26.com/fan-fest/ |publisher=FIFA |access-date=May 25, 2026 |quote=Centennial Olympic Park will become the official home of the FIFA Fan Festival Atlanta, transforming one of the city’s most iconic public spaces into a lively gathering place where fans, families, and visitors come together to celebrate the game.}}</ref> and [[East Downtown Houston]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jenkins |first1=Cassandra |title=EaDo selected as site for 2026 FIFA World Cup Fan Festival; officials lay out preparation plan for games |url=https://communityimpact.com/houston/bay-area/sports/2024/06/11/eado-selected-as-site-for-2026-fifa-world-cup-fan-festival-officials-lay-out-preparation-plan-for-games/ |access-date=March 25, 2025 |work=CommunityImpact |date=June 11, 2024|archive-date=June 22, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240622130659/https://communityimpact.com/houston/bay-area/sports/2024/06/11/eado-selected-as-site-for-2026-fifa-world-cup-fan-festival-officials-lay-out-preparation-plan-for-games/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Tickets===
{{See also|List of 2026 FIFA World Cup controversies#Ticket prices}}

Ticket prices for the 2026 FIFA World Cup initially ranged from $60 for group stage matches to $6,730 for the final—largely increased from the USD equivalent of $69 to $1,607 in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]. However, in September 2025, FIFA confirmed it would use [[dynamic pricing]] for tickets for the first time, following the practice used in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=September 3, 2025 |title=FIFA to use dynamic pricing for World Cup tickets |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/46147005/2026-world-cup-tickets-fifa-dynamic-pricing-prices |access-date=September 3, 2025 |website=ESPN.com}}</ref> Hospitality seats were made available in April 2025 via FIFA's ticket partner for the event.<ref>{{Cite web |date=May 6, 2025 |title=Limited initial release of FIFA World Cup 26 hospitality packages for matches in United States launched |url=https://inside.fifa.com/tournament-organisation/commercial/news/limited-initial-release-of-fifa-world-cup-26-tm-hospitality-packages-for |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20250714204258/https://inside.fifa.com/tournament-organisation/commercial/news/limited-initial-release-of-fifa-world-cup-26-tm-hospitality-packages-for |archive-date=July 14, 2025 |access-date=May 20, 2026 |website=FIFA}}</ref>

An initial draw period for non-hospitality seats occurred between September 10–19, 2025, limited to [[Visa Inc.|Visa]] cardholders. A second phase ran from October 27–31, and a third phase started after the final draw of teams on December 5. Sales are capped at four tickets per person per match, and no person is able to purchase more than 40 tickets for the overall tournament. FIFA's official resale platform went live on October 2, 2025.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=September 30, 2025 |title=FIFA Resale/Exchange Marketplace |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/resale-ticket-exchange-marketplace |access-date=May 20, 2026 |website=FIFA}}</ref>

A final "last-minute" sales phase reopened on April 22, 2026, approximately 50 days before the start of the tournament, with tickets for all 104 matches made available on a first-come, first-served basis. By that stage, more than five million tickets had been sold out of an expected total exceeding six million, with additional tickets scheduled to be released in phases up to the final, subject to availability.<ref name="Reuters042226">{{cite news |title=World Cup last-minute ticket sales phase re-opens 50 days from kick-off |work=Reuters |date=April 22, 2026 |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/world-cup-last-minute-ticket-sales-phase-re-opens-50-days-kick-off-2026-04-22/ |access-date=April 27, 2026}}</ref>

Every city hosting the World Cup in the United States has passed a law stating that ticket sales to World Cup events are exempt from state and local sales taxes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://revisor.mo.gov/main/OneSection.aspx?section=144.051&bid=51142|title=144.051|website=revisor.mo.gov}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Wilson |first=Jonathan |date=April 2, 2026 |title=More than half of World Cup countries face extra costs as Fifa fails to agree US tax deal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/apr/02/world-cup-countries-face-extra-costs-fifa-tax-deal-us-government |work=The Guardian |access-date=April 2, 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gray |first=Page |date=December 5, 2025 |title=Not-So-Free Kick: How the 2026 FIFA World Cup Will Cost Cities Millions |url=https://itep.org/fifa-2026-world-cup-tickets-sales-tax-exemption/ |work=Institute on Taxation and Economic Policy |access-date=April 2, 2026}}</ref>

